description: From Medieval Ancient Greek μυσταγωγικός (mustagōgikós), corresponding to mystagogue +‎ -ic.

adjectives.description: mystagogic (comparative more mystagogic, superlative most mystagogic)

entries.meaning: Of or relating to mystagogy. [from 17th c.]
examples: ‘…this tiny element, with all his vigour of thought, would even today still hold him fast in his mystagogic camp!’
